---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_AUTHOR } from '@/consts';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-primary)] font-medium mb-2 tracking-wide uppercase">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-3">About Me</h1>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
        Network Engineer | Diver | Tech & Life Blogger
      </p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose max-w-none">
      <p>Hello everyone! I’d like to start with a short introduction.</p>

      <h2>👨‍💻 Professional Background</h2>
      <p>
        My name is Alex, and I work as a network engineer. I earned my CCIE certification in 2015, and I have been working in the networking field for nearly ten years.
      </p>

      <h2>🤿 Life & Hobbies</h2>
      <p>
        Outside of work, I am an active diver. I hold a <strong>PADI Advanced Open Water (AOW)</strong> certification and an <strong>AIDA 2</strong> freediving certification. I believe I am a reliable and safety-conscious dive buddy, so feel free to reach out if you’re looking for someone to dive with!
      </p>
      <p>
        I enjoy meeting new people and hope to make friends from all over the world. I would love to hear different stories, learn about different cultures, and experience different ways of life.
      </p>

      <h2>✍️ Why This Blog?</h2>
      <p>
        English is an important skill for me, both professionally and personally. However, I have never felt entirely confident in it. That is why I decided to build this blog and write in English regularly—I hope this habit will help me improve step by step.
      </p>

      <p>
        The main purpose of this blog is to document my daily life and share technical notes. If I can also connect with new friends through this space, that would be amazing!
      </p>

      <h2>📫 Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        If you would like to share your thoughts, discuss tech, or just say hi, feel free to leave a comment or send me an email. I promise I will read and reply to every single message!
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>